You check decaf or whipped cream, and you get caffeinated and no whip. You purchase blueberry oatmeal, and you get regular oatmeal.  One time I even managed to reach the manager by phone and walked him through the order - and they still got it wrong.  I know they are capable of following direction. Because when you order in person, you don’t need to supervise them and they manage to get it right.  It’s all just so unprofessional and inexcusable.  So if you want your order right, you will have to go to the place and order. For some, this won’t always be possible. But, obviously, they don’t care about losing business.
